    <p>DAWN RESSEL: Well, I, you know, first heard about the march on Facebook after the election. And many of my friends were feeling despair and fear about what would happen next in our country. And I saw this as an opportunity to become part of a community, a large community of people, like-minded people who want to stand up for what we believe is right.</p>
    <p>MARTIN: And, Dawn, is what - who's standing up for what you believe is right. Dawn, I'm so sorry.</p>
    <p>RESSEL: That's OK.</p>
