    <p>PYLE: The bottom line is that this president welcomes infrastructure projects, including projects that move our oil and gas resources around the country.</p>
    <p>BRADY: And in TransCanada's case, that's moving crude from Alberta's oil sands south to refineries on the Gulf Coast. This does not mean TransCanada will have an easy path to approval because there's more than the federal government involved. Jane Kleeb heads Bold Alliance, the group that led a campaign to block approval of the pipeline in Nebraska.</p>
