    <p>As word spread that President Trump was going to scale back the refugee program, something that Frank Gaffney had promoted, it was bad news for Rutland's mayor, Christopher Louras.</p>
    <p>UNIDENTIFIED WOMAN: Say this again.</p>
    <p>CHRISTOPHER LOURAS: We are done.</p>
    <p>UNIDENTIFIED WOMAN: OK.</p>
    <p>LOURAS: (Unintelligible). It's done.</p>
    <p>AMOS: At a local cafe, the mayor explains to his supporters that the two Syrian families that have arrived are probably the last. Sandy Gartner breaks down in tears.</p>
    <p>SANDY GARTNER: There are some of us want them.</p>
